Author: attickdoor
Name: Ability Ants
Description: For the WoW player who can't live without WeakAuras lighting up a button when it's off CD. /pants to configure.
Punchline: Draw ants when things are off cooldown.

Author: Ottermandias
Name: Accountant
Description:
Keep track of retainer, airship, submersible, aetherial wheel and crop timers
as well as several miscallaneous tasks of multiple characters.
Punchline: Character task timers.

Author: Tischel
Name: ActionTimeline
Description: Configurable timeline display of all the actions you use.
Punchline: Show your actions in real-time.
Changelog:
# 1.3.0.1

- Fixed Samurai's Kaeshi: Namikiri not showing correctly on the timeline.
- Fixed several Ninja actions not showing correctly on the timeline.

Author: Helios
Name: Adaptive Hud
Description:
Useful for ultrawide users, swapping from windowed/fullscreen will automatically switch your hudlayout.

/pah to configure
Punchline: Switches your /hudlayout when your game switches from windowed to fullscreen.

Author: Caraxi
Name: Adventurer in Need
Description: Receive a notification when a duty roulette is in need of a role. /pbonus to setup
Punchline: Receive a notification when a duty roulette is in need of a role.

Author: UnknownX
Name: A Realm Recorded
Description: Adds additional features to the duty recorder and automatically starts it in most instances.
Punchline: Allows you to use the duty recorder

Author: Gotest
Name: Audible Character Status
Description:
Plays a sound for certain statuses of the player. Such as low HP or MP.
You will need to provide your own sound files.
Punchline: You like annoying low HP sounds? This is great for you!
Changelog: Updated for API 9.

Author: Rietty
Name: AutoMammet
Description: Provides an easy copy and pastable CSV format you can use for island sanctuary spreadsheets. Provides options to export the popularity, future popularity and the current cycle's supply and demand shift values. Both as words and as numbers on a scale of -2 to 2. This plugin does not provide any calculations for Island Sanctuary, merely an export option for your ingame data. Information is exported to your clipboard, so you can paste into any other program.
Punchline: Provides an easy copy and pastable CSV format you can use for island sanctuary spreadsheets.

Author: VariableVixen
Name: AutoMountBgm
Description: Some mounts have really cool BGM tracks (Cruise Chaser FTW) while others are almost sickening in how much you hear them. It's annoying to keep needing to use /mountbgm, but now you won't have to - just let the plugin do it for you!
Punchline: Automatically control mount BGM for individual mounts!

Author: zhudotexe
Name: PaissaHouse
Description:
Looking for that perfect house? PaissaHouse lets you receive notifications when a new plot of land is up for sale on your home world.
View the list of all houses available on a world at https://paissadb.zhu.codes/!

Want to contribute? Check out the repository (globe icon below) for instructions.
Punchline: Crowdsourced housing alerts and lottery tracking for all.

Author: Aly
Name: AutoTimer
Description: Auto-Attack Timer Bar based on the Triggernometry trigger by aya liz.
Punchline: Auto-Attack Timer Bar.

Author: NeNeppie
Name: Avant-Garde
Description:
This plugin is a crowdsourced project, aiming to provide a comprehensive list for all hint categories.
See the github page for information on how you can contribute.
Punchline: Displays a list of valid gear pieces beside hints in the Fashion Report minigame.

Author: Kaz Wolfe
Name: BatteryGauge
Description:
Hey, you! Yes, you! Do you play FFXIV on your laptop or Steam Deck? Or are you so addicted to FFXIV that you have a UPS on your desktop just so you can keep playing through power outages? Then this is the plugin for you!

BatteryGauge adds a battery indicator to your server info bar showing your current battery percentage and expected remaining lifespan (as reported by Windows).
Punchline: Keep track of your FFXIV device's battery.

Author: NotNite
Name: Better in Blue
Description: Allows you to save, load, and share infinite Blue Mage spell loadouts.
Punchline: Infinite Blue Mage spell loadouts.

Author: Nuffin
Name: Better Mount Roulette
Description: Allows any number of mounts to be enabled for the mount roulette, instead of having to choose between the "up to 30" and "EVERYTHING" modes supported by the game.
Punchline: Choose which mounts show up in the mount roulette.

Author: Anna
Name: Better Party Finder
Description:
Filter the party finder better.

All vanilla filtering is available, plus:

- Create filter presets to easily switch between
- Whitelist/blacklist specific duties and categories
- Add character names to hide PFs from
- Remove PFs above maximum item level
- Filter on item level range
- Filter on multiple jobs and slots (ex. MCH + GNB available)
Punchline: Use advanced Party Finder filter presets.

Author: Infi
Name: Better Playtime
Description:
Provides expanded functionality to seamlessly track total playtime.
      Use /btime once on each character to add them.

      - Supports multiple characters,
      - Customisable output formats such as hours or minutes
      - Automatic playtime tracking after character got registered
      - Simple window to see current session playtime
      - Server Info Bar integration
Punchline: Ever wanted detailed information on your playtime all the way down to the second?

Author: Drahsid
Name: Better Shadows
Description: Directly adjust the distance of each shadow cascade! Now introducing 4k shadowmap!
Punchline: Take control of your shadows!

Author: d87
Name: BigPlayerDebuffs
Description: Scales up buffs/debuffs applied by you on Target Status frames
Punchline: Larger personal debuffs
Changelog:
* v1.1.0.9
 * 6.5 Dalamud Update

Author: Infi, Sl0nderman
Name: Blue Mage Helper
Description: Adds monster names and coordinates to the "Where to Learn" section of your blue mage spellbook.
Punchline: Helps you fill out your Blue Mage Spellbook

Author: veyn
Name: Better borderless window mode
Description: Borderless window can now be properly minimized (by clicking on taskbar or by win+down shortcut); when moved between monitors (win+shift+left/right), resolution is updated automatically.
Punchline: Make borderless window mode work well with aero shortcuts

Author: K-Cli
Name: Bozja Buddy
Description:
Features:
• Resistance relic guide and tracking.
• Info about Lost Actions, Fragments, FATEs/CE, Field Notes e.g. location, drops, marketboard price, fate chains, mettle rewards, exp rewards, etc.
• Node graph viewer.
• Weather forecast.
• Alarms based on time, weather, and FATE/CE.
• Custom loadouts planning, saving, and sharing. Featuring recommended loadouts from many communities.
• Overlay for Lost Find Cache. Filterable by name, role, fragment, weight, and Custom Loadout of choice.
• View Bozja stats and Cache from anywhere. Customisable alert for actions that are running low.
• Delubrum Reginae (Savage) resources and communities.
Punchline: Improve your Bozja sufferring. Maybe.

Author: Styr1x
Name: Browsingway
Description:
Renders browser overlays in-game to enable playing in fullscreen (and G-SYNC) while having access to ACT overlays.
Use the settings button below or the '/bw config' command to configure.
Based on the BrowserHost plugin by ackwell.
Punchline: Browser overlays rendered in-game.
Changelog:
- Chromium 122.0.6261.112
- Option to hide overlays out of combat (by electr0sheep)
- .net 8 support
- IPC refactoring

Author: X'pahtalo (originally Anna)
Name: Burnt Toast
Description: Hides toast notifications you don't want to see.
Punchline: Hides toast notifications you don't want to see.

Author: Kouzukii
Name: Character Panel Refined
Description: Character Panel Refined cuts away useless information from the character panel, while adding useful stats like critical hit and direct hit percentages as well as estimates damage output to allow for easier comparison of gear.
Punchline: Refine the character panel to display only useful information like crit and direct hit chance

Author: Caraxi & Ottermandias
Name: ChatAlerts
Punchline: Play sounds and highlight text based on defined filters.

Author: Haplo064, Khayle
Name: Chat Bubbles
Description: Using native chat bubble display, see who is talking about what in a more natural fashion.
Punchline: Enables in-game chat bubbles.

Author: kij
Name: ChatCoordinates
Description:
Places flag marker on map from coordinates in chat.
Opens map with given coordinates for current or given zone.
See "/coord" for configuration and usage info.
Punchline: Places flag marker on map from coordinates in chat.

Author: kelvin124124
Name: ChatTranslated
Description: Ingame chat translator.
Punchline: Ingame chat translator.

Author: Infi, Anna
Name: Chat 2
Description:
Chat 2 is a complete rewrite of the in-game chat window as a plugin.
It supports:

- Unlimited tabs
- Tabs that always send to a certain channel
- More flexible filtering
- RGB channel colouring
- Completely variable font size
- Sidebar tabs
- Unread counts
- Emotes
- Screenshot mode (obfuscate names)
Punchline: Electric Boogaloo - ♪ A whole new chat, a new fantastic chat window ♪
Changelog:
**Updates**
- Fix tell reply hotkey not working
- Save the FFXIV font to disk instead of redownloading it on every startup
  - This should prevent errors if your DNS is giving up
- Replace all sigs with CS version
- Fix flags not working in reply mode
- Force the main chat log to be always open
- Prevent emotes inside auto translation
- Linkshells appear in selection again
- Fix rotate mode not working for CW and Normal Linkshells

Author: Franz
Name: ChatTyper
Description: Prefixes all chatbox messages with their chat type number and name, if known.
Punchline: This is still mostly a dev tool for debugging, but people like it?

Author: MidoriKami
Name: Chill Frames
Description: Tired of your GPU melting your face off while just running around? Why render at 240 FPS when you're just staring at that gathering node? Fret no more! Chill Frames allows you dynamically limit your framerate when doing unimportant tasks!
Punchline: Limit Framerate while out of combat

Author: NotNite
Name: cl_showpos
Description: Shows your exact position, rotation, and velocity on screen. Based off of the cl_showpos command from the Source Engine.
Punchline: Customizable, Source Engine-styled position info

Author: Meoiswa
Name: Clarity In Chaos
Description: Automatically adjusts the Battle Effects settings according to Party size.
Punchline: Seek visual serenity in the midst of Chaos

Author: Liza Carvelli
Name: CollectableCalculator
Description: Shows how many scrips and items you would receive if you turn in your current inventory.
Punchline: Shows how many scrips and items you would receive if you turn in your current inventory.

Author: Seventh
Name: Collections
Description:
Collections provides an interface to track, discover and interact with your Collections in game.
Integrates with Glamour systems (Preview, Create Sets, Glamour Plates).
Supports: Glamour, Mounts, Minions, Emotes, Hairstyles, Triple Triad, Blue Mage, Bardings.
Punchline: Track, Discover and Interact with your Collections in game

Author: Cytraen
Name: Combat Cursor Containment
Description: Automatically changes the 'limit mouse operation to game window' setting when entering/exiting combat.
Punchline: Keep your mouse cursor contained during combat!
Changelog: - Fixes for log spam and cursor being locked when alt+tabbed due to recent Dalamud changes.

Author: Chivalrik
Name: Compass
Description:
Check-out the repository for steps on how to report missing/wrong filter
and hiding options. Have a look at the FAQ tab in the config window
after install for common caveats.
Punchline: Monodimensional compass for your adventures.
Changelog:
- chore: Update to API 9
- fix: More icons handled

Author: Berna
Name: Congratulations
Description:
Get aurally rewarded when you get commended on duties.

Comes with default sounds for when you get commended by 1/3, 2/3, 3/3 or all seven members of the duty you were in, but you can set custom sounds for each type of trigger by opening /congratsconfig.

The fractioned values are in relation to how many of those members could commend you (i.e. excluding those that were in your party before joining the duty).
Punchline: Get aurally rewarded when you get commended on duties.

Author: kelvin124124
Name: CopyTranslated
Description: Copy translated item name by right-clicking.
Punchline: Copy translated item name by right-clicking.

Author: Asriel
Name: Craftimizer
Description: Allows you to generate macros and simulate all sorts of crafts without having to open another app. Open your crafting log to get started!
Punchline: Simulate crafts, create computer-assisted macros, and get mid-craft suggestions from the comfort of your own game!

Author: ItsBexy
Name: CrossUp
Description:
This plugin provides various customizations for the look and feel of the Cross Hotbar.

-Split up the left/right hotbars
-Display Expanded Hold Controls Separately
-Customize colors and element positions
-Greater control over which sets your extra bars are mapped to
Punchline: Customize the Cross Hotbar!

Author: MidoriKami, Lharz
Name: CurrencyAlert
Description: This plugin lets you easily manage your various currencies to prevent from wasting precious resources.
Punchline: Display alerts upon reaching configurable currencies thresholds.

Author: AtmoOmen
Name: Currency Tracker
Description:
Track changes of currencies with Time, Location and Note(Source)!

Also provide something like queries, exporting, adding custom currencies tracker and viewing visualized data.
Punchline: Track all your currencies!

Author: MidoriKami
Name: Daily Duty
Description: Automatically track and complete many daily and weekly tasks.
Punchline: Easily Track Daily and Weekly tasks

Author: goat
Name: Character Data Sync
Description:
This plugin allows you to use your character data from your main character on all others.

In-game, use the configuration menu to choose your main character, the restart the game to start syncing!
Punchline: Sync your character data from your main character to all others

Author: goat, modded by Franz
Name: Discord Chat Bridge
Description: This plugin allows you to receive your chat messages via Discord.
Punchline: Receive your chat messages via Discord.
Changelog: Updated for 6.5 / API 9

Author: goat
Name: Wotsit
Description:
Adds a convenient quick search akin to Spotlight that lets you open game windows, teleport, find wiki articles, and more.
Press Control + T to open the search window. This can be changed by searching for "Wotsit Settings".
Punchline: Find anything, go anywhere, in style.

Author: goat
Name: Ultrawide Cutscenes
Description:
This plugin removes the "letterboxing" bars when watching cutscenes on ultrawide monitors.
Beware! You may see things that you are not supposed to be seeing, such as upcoming NPCs popping in or T-posing.

Thanks to aers for finding this.
Punchline: Remove letterboxing from cutscenes on ultrawide monitors.

Author: goat
Name: Fancy Loading Screens
Description:
This plugin shows the destination zone's concept art while loading.
NOTE: ONLY LOOKS RIGHT ON 16:9 SCREENS! The concept art is not any bigger, and we can't expand/fix it. Sorry!
Punchline: Shows the destination zone's concept art while loading

Author: goat
Name: Discord Rich Presence
Description: This plugin allows you to show your zone, job, level, name, and world in your Discord status.
Punchline: Show your zone, job, level, name, and world in your Discord status
Changelog: API 7 compatibility

Author: hunter2_
Name: Minesweeper
Description:
Logic puzzle in which you find and flag hidden mines. 
Left click to uncover a square, right click to place a flag. 
Click a number that has the right number of flags to reveal adjacent tiles. 
The game ends when all mines are flagged and all safe squares have been uncovered. 
Click the smiley face to start a new game.
Punchline: Classic puzzle game.

Author: perchbird
Name: Damage Info
Description: Configurable options for in-game fly text color based on damage type, with additional settings for damage source and fly text decluttering options.
Punchline: Modifies in-game fly-text for more (or less) damage information.

Author: Kouzukii
Name: Death Recap
Description:
Quickly figure out what killed you or your party members!

Shows:
- Healing
- Damage taken
- Debuffs
- Buffs
- Barriers
- Addle, Feint, Reprisal on damage source
Punchline: Quickly figure out what killed you or your party members!

Author: Infi
Name: Death Roll Helper
Description:
## Modes
### Venue:
- Concise display of all concurrent players in a list-based format
- Supports multiple sorting types (min, max, nearest to)
- Highlight numbers based on regex matching

### DeathRoll:
- Supports multiple players
- Automatic checks to prevent number skipping

### Tournament (1v1 DeathRoll):
- Automatic bracket generation with byes to fill uneven
- Forfeit functionality if a player needs to leave

### Blackjack:
- Automatic reward calculation based on common rules
- Simplistic, or visual view of cards in play
- Automatic or manual player-based draw for cards

### Extra Features:
- Block or prevent players from partaking in any game
- Accept only /random or /dice commands

## Games
### Tic-Tac-Toe
- Play against your friends, or AI
- Easy, Medium, Hard
- 3x3, 4x4, 5x5

### Minesweeper
- Easy, Medium, Hard
- 8x8, 9x9, 16x16, 18x30
- Custom Games (planned)

More features are planned, following user feedback.
Punchline: Plugin to help with a number of dice games. Also offers games like Tic-Tac-Toe, Minesweeper and Bahamood.

Author: WildWolf
Name: DeepDungeonDex
Description:
A live bestiary for Deep Dungeon.
Shows target mob aggro type, a subjective threat level, status vulnerabilities, and a general overview of notable mechanics.
Threat level is meant to be taken with a grain of salt, is aimed towards solo players, and assumes a general familiarity with deep dungeon mechanics and the class being played.
Information is accurate to the best of my knowledge based on crowdsourced information, but I could use your help! Please open an issue on the GitHub if you'd like to correct inaccurate or untested data.
Original by Strati
Punchline: Live monster data for Deep Dungeons.

Author: Marconsou
Name: Deep Dungeon Tracker
Description:
-Keep track of the number of kills, coffers opened, regeneration potions consumed, potsherds obtained, total time and more.
-Examine the collected data.
-Scoring.
Punchline: Track things inside Deep Dungeons (Solo only).

Author: Tischel
Name: DelvCD
Description: DelvCD provides highly customizable UI elements that can be used to track cooldows, status and more with configurable conditions.
Punchline: Customizable UI elements to track cooldowns, status and more.

Author: Tischel
Name: DelvUI
Description: DelvUI provides a highly configurable HUD replacement and is highly inspired by ElvUI from WoW
Punchline: A modern HUD replacement built for customization.

Author: Jessidhia
Name: DeviceChangeFix
Description:
Stops controller input from freezing randomly by ensuring FFXIV only polls for controllers when one is actually connected or disconnected.

Original plugin by PGGB, icon from Mutant Standard.
Punchline: Stops controller input from freezing randomly.

Author: Infi, mudcrab2142
Name: Diadem Calculator
Description: Calculates your current sessions points and scrip reward
Punchline: Yet another useful calculator~

Author: PunishedPineapple
Name: Distance
Description:
Displays the distance in yalms to your target and/or other enemies, players, NPCs, etc.  It can also display the aggro range for supported bosses.
Please note that this plugin automatically downloads updates for aggro data by default.  This can be disabled in the plugin settings if you wish.
Punchline: Target distance widgets.

Author: NotNite
Name: Distant Seas
Description:
The ultimate Ocean Fishing plugin. Automatically suggests baits, logs each boat you're on, tracks progress to achievements, adds a global point leaderboard, and more!

Icon from the Mutant Standard project.
Punchline: The ultimate Ocean Fishing plugin.

Author: SoyaX
Name: Doorbell
Description:
Play a chime when someone comes into a house, when they leave or when entering a house people are already inside.

Icon by Flaticon
Punchline: Play a chime when someone comes into a house.

Author: X'pahtalo
Name: Duty Tracker
Description: Track some duty info. /dt open the menu
Punchline: Track some duty info.

Author: ocealot
Name: EasyEyes
Description: A plugin which can hide any VFX. Icon by PAPACHIN
Punchline: Hide annoying or distracting VFXs

Author: Olaren
Name: Easy Translate
Description:
Search anything and get the translations in other languages.
Use /et to open the ui or /et <search term> to search directly!
Punchline: Translate anything!

Author: lokinmodar
Name: Echoglossian
Description: Realtime game text translator
Punchline:
Dialogue and other in-game text translations? Yes we have!
Known Issues at: https://github.com/lokinmodar/Echoglossian/issues/12

Author: Fools by Goat, taken over by Roselyn, on life support by Franz
Name: Elden Ring April Fools
Description: Currently under development with extra features, should currently function as the April Fools joke did.
Punchline: Recreation of the Elden Ring April Fools joke.

Author: Speedas
Name: Emote log
Description: Adds a window logging all emotes used on you, so you never miss a sneaky dote again.
Punchline: Track who used what emotes on you.

Author: Felys & Anima
Name: EnemyListDebuffs
Description: Displays your debuffs on the enemy list. Original implementation credit to aers.
Punchline: Because tracking your DoTs shouldn't be difficult.

Author: Xorus
Name: EngageTimer
Description:
Finally, display all the numbers when starting a countdown!
Comes with an accurate pull timer that starts when you or any of your party members enter combat.

Features :
- Big countdown that displays all the numbers
- Customizable big-number textures (default, yellow, WoW style or custom files)
- Display combat time in the Server Info Bar, and/or a floating window
- OBS browser-source compatible page with countdown and current combat duration

Why the OBS thing ? I like having a big stylized stopwatch in my private recordings and that's about it.
See repository for more info.

Feel free so send me feedback, bugs and potential improvements! Check the about page in the plugin settings for more
info. Please report urgent feedback on GitHub or XIVLauncher Discord's support thread for this plugin.
Punchline: Complete combat countdown, pull timer and OBS overlay
Changelog:
- Fix not being able to disable alarms
- Missing translation strings in web server config
- Hide floating window border by default (you can re-enable it in Floating Window -> styling)

Author: NightmareXIV
Name: EnemyListHP (former EnmityHp)
Description: Displays enemies hp in enemy list. Just does that, nothing else.
Punchline: Displays enemies hp in enemy list.

Author: Anna
Name: Eorzea Votes
Description: Cast your vote in daily lighthearted opinion polls!
Punchline: Cast your vote in daily lighthearted opinion polls! Is a hot dog a sandwich?

Author: Snowy
Name: Eureka Helper
Description:
A tool to assist you on your Eureka adventures. Type /eurekahelper to get started.

Features include:
- In-Game Tracker GUI
- Instance Tracker
- Elementals Tracker
- Relic Helper
- Alarms
- Money NM weather timings
- More to come
Punchline: Eureka Tracker in a plugin with many other features.

Author: Infi, electr0sheep
Name: Eureka Linker
Description:
Automatically notifies you about NMs in Eureka, with the ability to pop them on a tracker.
Other Features:
- Fairy Finder
- Bunny Timer Window
- Bunny Coffer Helper
- Stats
- Quest Guide (clickable coords)
- Localized (DE, FR, JA)
Punchline: Help, Link and Pop

Author: Anna
Name: Expanded Search Info
Description:
Displays extra information pulled from search info when examining.

Support for:
- Any plain text URL
- Pastebin.com
- carrd.co/crd.co
- F-List
- Refsheet

Simply examine someone with a search info containing pointers to one of
these locations and the plugin will display information automatically.

Icon: expand by Gregor Cresnar from the Noun Project
Punchline: Displays extra information pulled from search info when examining.

Author: Anna
Name: ExtraChat
Description:
ExtraChat adds end-to-end encrypted, cross-data-centre, unlimited linkshells
to the game.
Punchline: Cross-data-centre linkshells with unlimited members.

Author: shdwp, Aelexe, maintained by Infi
Name: Fader Plugin
Description: Lets you automatically hide certain game UI elements based on number of conditions.
Punchline: Automatically hides UI elements.

Author: Critical-Impact
Name: Fantasy Player
Description:
Control Spotify playback from within FFX|V
Use the button below to open settings or use the '/pfp settings' command.
Originally by BiscuitUmU
Localization by Dormanil
Punchline: Like you'd ever be sick of the in game music right?

Author: Meoiswa
Name: Fast Job Switcher
Description: Enables the player to switch jobs using their three letter acronyms as commands. (*: five or more)
Punchline: Always five* keystrokes away from any job

Author: daemitus
Name: ezFauxHollows
Description: This plugin highlights tiles in Faux Hollows that represent the best potential action you can take.
Punchline: Highlights recommended tiles in Faux Hollows for your next move.

Author: CFG
Name: FC Name Color
Description:
Color your FC’s tag or the entire nameplate if they are in your FC or other specified FCs.
Works using Lodestone data, so it can continue working inside duties as well as on different servers!
Punchline: Color your FC member’s FC tags
FeedbackMessage: Please include your character’s name and server if you’re reporting a bug or issue. This helps a lot with the troubleshooting process.

Author: X'pahtalo
Name: FFXIV2MQTT
Description: Send data to an MQTT broker to do all sorts of things. Change your lights with a macro, turn on the heater when you use Overheat, or start playing Rules of Nature when you switch to Gunbreaker. Requires an MQTTv5 compatible broker.
Punchline: Send game info over MQTT

Author: erroch
Name: FFXIV RP Event Calendar
Description: An in game portal to the FFXIV RP Event Calendar (https://ffxiv-rp.org).  Use /events to bring up the list of roleplay events happening this week.
Punchline: Want to know what's going in in roleplay today?

Author: Franz
Name: FlashOnTell
Description: Flash FFXIV's program on the taskbar when you receive a /tell. This plugin has no configurable settings at this time.
Punchline: Flash FFXIV's program on the taskbar when you receive a /tell

Author: Aireil
Name: FlyTextFilter
Description: Filter fly texts and pop-ups texts based on multiple criteria and allow the adjustment of their positions.
Punchline: Filter fly texts and pop-ups texts based on multiple criteria and allow the adjustment of their positions.

Author: Caraxi
Name: FPS Plugin
Description: Display game FPS. It really is that simple.
Punchline: Display game FPS.

Author: img02
Name: Fungah
Description:
Guaranteed to be safe, unless it isn't. No refunds. 

[ Any Way the Wind Blows (Fungah) is a Gold Saucer Gate 
  There are variations of AOE patterns that can occur 
  There is no real 'safe spot', but there are spaces where there is less overlap by these potential AOEs 
  One of these spots is marked by this plugin when you are in the GATE ]
Punchline: south spot best spot

Author: justscribe
Name: G4E UkrChatSupport
Description: Support for ukrainian characters in text chat and input field.
Punchline: Support for ukrainian characters.

Author: Ottermandias
Name: GatherBuddy
Description:
Adds commands to simplify gathering by finding nodes and fish and their locations
via item name and a UI to keep track of special uptime and weather conditions.
Punchline: Simplify Gathering and Fishing.

Author: Khloe Leclair
Name: Gearset Helper Plugin
Description: Displays extra information about a character's gearsets when Examine is open, and makes it easy to export gearsets to Etro or Ariyala.
Punchline: Display estimated stats with Examine, and export gear to Etro/Ariyala.

Author: Chivalrik
Name: GentleTouch
Description:
You need to configure patterns and triggers before it will work, 
open the configuration window to do that.  

For DualSense/Shock4 support, the controller needs to be connected wired (same as the game's)
and there can only be one of a type connected (e.g., only one DualSense, not two).

Currently supported triggers are:
- Cooldowns
- Near Aether Current
Punchline: Create vibration patterns for the controller and specify triggers to make it vibrate.
Changelog:
- chore: Update to API 9
- feat (wip!): Use DualSense adaptive triggers to mimic double tapping (EXPERIMENTAL)

Author: Anna
Name: Glamaholic
Description:
Create and save as many glamour plates as you want. Activate up to 15 of them
at once at the Glamour Dresser. Supports exporting and importing plates for
easy sharing.
Punchline: Save and swap your glamour plates.

Author: Anna
Name: Globetrotter
Description:
Automatically shows where treasure maps are located.

Icon: Map by Adrien Coquet from the Noun Project
Punchline: Automatically shows where treasure maps are located.

Author: tesu
Name: Penny Pincher
Description:
Plugin for simplifying "pennying" (undercutting current lowest offer by 1).

The usual workflow for this is the following:
1. Open up the adjust price menu for the item you're undercutting
2. Click on the compare prices menu to view the current listings
3. Take a mental note of what the current lowest offer is
4. Subtract one from it
5. Close the current listings window
6. Update your item's price with the number you noted
7. Confirm your new price

This plugin eliminates the mental notekeeping steps in the middle by automatically copying the number you want onto your clipboard when you open the current listings window.  

Therefore, your new workflow becomes this:
1. Open up the adjust price menu for the item you're undercutting
2. Click on the compare prices menu to view the current listings
3. Close the current listings window
4. Paste the undercut value in
5. Confirm your new price

This both speeds up the process and reduces room for error from typos.
Punchline: Copies 1 below the cheapest offer to your clipboard when you check marketboard prices
Changelog: API version bump

Name: SoundSetter
Description: A Dalamud plugin that allows volume control from anywhere, including gpose and cutscenes.
Punchline: A Dalamud plugin that allows volume control from anywhere, including gpose and cutscenes.

Author: VariableVixen
Name: StackSellPrice
Description: Shows the vendor sell price for the full stack of an item on the tooltip
Punchline: Because multiplication is hard.

Author: rekyuu
Name: Stanley Parable XIV
Description: Check /narrator for full options or use /narratorvolume to set volume manually.
Punchline: Witty commentary to the brilliant things you do.

Author: Chickenstew
Name: Stormtalons
Description: Gives the value of current targets health in Stormtalons from the dead game Wildstar.
Punchline: Gives the value of current targets health in Stormtalons from the dead game Wildstar.

Author: Infi
Name: Submarine Tracker
Description:
+ Tracker for current builds, routes and times 
+ Builder to improve, solve builds and optimize EXP
+ Configurable notification for return and repairs 
+ Helpy filled useful information
+ Custom loot overview with history and export
+ Multiple overlays to help with daily tasks 
+ Supports multiple FCs
Punchline: You do not talk about Fight Club, same for Submarines

Author: Glyceri
Name: Dialog Copy
Description: Automatically copies messages from the Dialog Box to your clipboard.
Punchline: Automatically copies messages from the Dialog Box to your clipboard.

Author: Det
Name: Target Furniture
Description:
Currently, the only possible way to select a housing item is to click the furniture itself, and this can be a problem if you have multiple items close to each other.

This plugin adds a new option in the Housing Menu that targets the furniture for you
Punchline: You can now select furnitures from the Housing Menu
Changelog: 6.5 update

Author: Drahsid
Name: Target Lines
Description: Customizable target lines
Punchline: Customizable target lines

Author: Pohky
Name: Teleporter
Description:
Adds Chat Commands to Teleport to Aetherytes or Areas by Name.
e.g. /tp Quarrymill or /tpm South Shroud
Supports setting up an Alias for Aetherytes to be used with Teleporter Commands
e.g. /tp home instead of /tp Estate Hall (Free Company)
Punchline: Chat Commands for Teleporting

Author: Anna
Name: Text Box Styler
Description: Allows replacing every text box with the background of your choice.
Punchline: Allows replacing every text box with the background of your choice.

Author: karashiiro
Name: TextToTalk
Description: Chat and game dialogue TTS. Use /tttconfig to configure the enabled channels and triggers/exceptions.
Punchline: Chat and game dialogue TTS plugin.

Author: Berna
Name: Hit it, Joe! (Formerly TF2-ish Critical Hits Plugin)
Description:
* Set sounds and flavor text to be played/shown whenever you deal direct or critical damage or heal.
* Set sounds to be played when a countdown is in progress.
* Use different configurations by job.
* Use the game's SFX or your own custom WAV or MP3 files.
Punchline: Configure sounds for critical and direct hits, plus some countdown music.

Author: Berna
Name: Team Fortress Fantasy
Description:
* Show a Win Panel (with sounds!) when you clear or get wiped in a duty.
* Show a TF2-style timer while in a duty.
* Enable the "Voice Lines" module (via /tfconfig) to have voice lines play when certain conditions are met. What conditions, you ask? It's a surprise! (Unless you uncheck the "Surprise me!" box.)
* More features maybe soon?

Note: This plugin uses files from a local Team Fortress 2 installation.
It'll search for the game's installation folder in all configured Steam Library Folders automatically.

Without a TF2 install, the Timer and Win Panel will work with FF XIV fonts, and no voice line will work.
Punchline:
[REQUIRES TF2 INSTALLED FOR MOST FEATURES] The Mann Brothers just found a deposit of gravel in Eorzea
and hired YOU, Mercenary of Light, to help them FIGHT for it.

Author: Anna
Name: The Great Separator
Description:
Add separators to various numbers.

- Damage/healing numbers (not DoTs or other players' numbers)
- Party list HP
- Ability costs on hotbars
- Ability costs in tooltips
Punchline: Add separators to various numbers.

Author: Anna
Name: The Heart of the Party
Description:
The Heart of the Party is a remake of the in-game title picker, but it
supports searching. Note that it doesn't add a command to set your title; use
the built-in /title command instead.
Punchline: Set your character's title - now with Searchalin!

Author: Kurochi
Name: Tick Tracker
Description: Customizable bars that indicate the tick progress of HP/MP/GP regen
Punchline: Tracks the current tick for HP/MP/GP regen

Author: Nadya
Name: Tidy Chat
Description:
It is highly recommended to edit the default settings as you may disagree on which messages should be considered "spam"!

Provides granular filter options to filter nearly all game-related spam, leaving only important game messages in your chat.

  - Filters most spammy game messages
  - Blocks emote spam from other players
  - Condenses earned commendations into a single line
  - Shortens lengthy messages such as joining Novice Network or entering an instanced zone
  - Blocks repeated messages from appearing for a period of time
  - Automatically copies most 'with your chat mode in /say' quest dialogue to your clipboard
  - Write custom filters to Allow/Block messages!
  - And more!
Punchline: Better game messages and in-depth chat filters to keep a tidy chat.

Author: Meoiswa
Name: Tilted
Description: Automatically adjusts the Third Person Camera Angle/Distance given certain conditions.
Punchline: Tilt the camera, not yourself.

Author: kalilistic
Name: Tippy
Description:
Developed by goat for April Fools 2021 and unnecessarily resurrected by kal.

Handcrafted by our finest code artisans with special AI, 
he will analyze your playstyle to give you useful tips to get your GAMING to the next level.

Some things he can do:
* He can give general tips about the game
* He can give tips about the job you're playing
* He can report on your battle performance
* He will respect your feelings
Punchline: Tippy, your new FFXIV virtual assistant.

Author: attick & perchbird
Name: Title Edit
Description:
Create your own custom title screen of your favorite location in-game, and open the game right up to that spot every time.
Includes a number of preinstalled title screens for you to use or get inspiration from, and an easy to use importer to
use title screens that others have shared!
Punchline: Create, share, and shuffle custom title screens for FFXIV.

Author: Liza Carvelli
Name: Title Roulette
Description: Allows you to pick any number of titles, setting a random one each time you use "/ptitle" or "/ptitle groupName".
Punchline: Pick titles you want in a title roulette.

Author: Lore
Name: TooltipNotes
Description: Right-click any item in your inventory to start adding a note,or make a label in the config window to start adding your own labels
Punchline: A Plugin that lets you add notes to item Tooltips

Author: Anna
Name: Tourist
Description:
Tourist adds a window to assist with the sightseeing log.

- Show when sightseeing log vistas are available
- Add markers for ARR vistas
- Open vista locations on your map
- Hide already completed or unavailable vistas
- Show the command needed for each vista

Icon: sightseeing by muhammad from the Noun Project
Punchline: Finish your sightseeing log.

Author: Tischel
Name: TPie
Description: Highly configurable hotbars that can be toggled with a keybind. They can be filled with Actions, Items, Gear Sets, Macros and more...
Punchline: Customizable ring-shaped hotbars
Changelog:
# 1.8.2.0

- The Escape key can now be used to close a ring with a toggable keybind.
- Added a setting for rings with toggable keybinds to not execute the hovered action when closed.

Author: Infi
Name: Tracky
Description:
### Normal Functions 
+ Track currency increase
+ Track teleport and npc repair costs
+ Track desynthesis results
+ Track retainer ventures

### Advanced  Functions
+ Track different coffer rewards
  - Venture Coffer
  - Materiel Container 3.0
  - Materiel Container 4.0
  - Sanctuary Materiel Container
+ Track Eureka bunny rewards
+ Track Eureka/Bozja lockboxes
Punchline: Tracking data is fun

Author: MgAl2O4
Name: TriadBuddy
Description:
Triple triad solver, NPC matches only.
- highlights next move during mini game
- evaluates all deck presets before match
- deck optimizer for NPC
- adds more details to card collection window
Punchline: Triple triad solver

Author: Aida Enna
Name: Twitch XIV
Description: Allows you to join a Twitch chat and send messages and (optionally) have the twitch chat come through your chatbox.
Punchline: Sup y'all? It's ya boy, Twitch XIV, and today we're gonna be playing some final fantasy fourteen.

Author: LittleNighmare
Name: Used Name
Description: A simple tool to record players' used names and nickname base on SocialList. Right click on the target to add/sub/check the used names and nickname.
Punchline: A simple tool to record players' used names and nickname

Author: ocealot
Name: VFXEditor
Description: VFX, animation, and sound editing plugin. Icon by PAPACHIN
Punchline: VFX editor and viewer

Author: Dragon
Name: Visibility
Description:
Allows you to hide players, pets, chocobos and minions.
Includes VoidList, which is a better blacklist.
Accessible via /pvis
More information available via /xlhelp
Punchline: Allows you to hide players, pets, chocobos and minions.

Author: Asriel
Name: Waitingway
Description:
Contributes and utilizes crowdsourced login queue information for the benefit of everyone.

Current features include queue time estimates and notifications via Discord, so you can know when you make it
into the game, as well as anonymously collecting and reporting statistics about your login queue times to crowdsource
information about FFXIV server load. Join our Discord for more information!

Discord URL: https://waiting.camora.dev/discord
Punchline: Set out for Dawntrail and make your queues a breeze. Waitingway provides crowdsourced FFXIV login queue times, now with Discord queue notification features.

Author: Infi, PunishedPineapple
Name: Waymark Preset Plugin
Description: Allows you to save, edit, place, import, export, and preview an unlimited number of waymark presets.
Punchline: Improved Waymark Management

Author: NightmareXIV
Name: Weatherman
Punchline: Allows precise control over time and weather per zone or globally.

Author: PunishedPineapple
Name: Say What?
Description: Prints NPC speech bubbles to the chat log.  Please check the plugin settings and your chat log filters to make sure that they are compatible with each other.
Punchline: Persistent NPC Flavor Text

Author: MidoriKami, cassandra308
Name: Where am I again?
Description: Shows what zone/region/territory you are in up in the corner next to the server and time info. Open config with /waia.
Punchline: Shows what zone/region/territory you are in next to the server info.

Author: Haplo064, maintained by Franz
Name: WOLdo
Description: Movable text overlay of the current location name. Please consider migrationg to WhereAmIAgain, which is actively maintained and has more features.
Punchline: Making it easier to know where you are.

Author: Kouzukii
Name: Which Patch Was That?
Description:
Whenever you mouseover an item, the tooltip will show you the patch the item was released in.
Never carry around old useless crafting materials again!
Punchline: Quickly check the patch an item was released in!

Author: MidoriKami
Name: Who am I again?
Description: Shows who you are in the server info bar.
Punchline: Ever forget who you are? We can fix that!

Author: spide-r
Name: Who Did That?
Description:
This plugin can track the following actions:
- Rescues
- Healing actions
- Status/Buff Application
- Cleanses 
- Heals
- Mitigation
- Provoke
- Shirk

These will be logged in your chat when they are used on your character.
Punchline: Actively logs healing, cleanses, buffs, and more. Finally figure out who rescued you.

Author: Blooym
Name: Wholist
Description:
Show nearby players in a stylish way, inspired by the "/who" command from World of Warcraft

Features:
- Minimalistic interface that can be scaled down to become part of your HUD.
- Player context menu items, like sending tells, examining, searching on the Lodestone and more.
- Customizable colours & behaviour.
- Integration support with other plugins via IPC.
Punchline: Show nearby players in a stylish way, inspired by the "/who" command from World of Warcraft.

Author: ash
Name: Who's Talking
Description:
Once installed, join a Discord voice channel and an XIV party, and have people put their character names in their Discord nicknames. You should get colourful outlines around the job icons on the party list: green for talking, blue for muted, red for deafened, and yellow for unknown name.

Note that you'll get a permission prompt mentioning "StreamKit Overlay" – this is expected.

If stuff breaks, let me know - click Send Feedback (speech bubble icon) below this text.
Punchline: See Discord voice activity indicators directly on your party list.

Author: Azure Gem
Name: Window Title Changer
Description: Allows you to change your game window title
Punchline: Change your game window titie

Author: daemitus, MidoriKami
Name: ezWondrousTails
Description: This plugin prints the probability of getting a row in Wondrous Tails to the in-game display along with the average probability of what would happen if you shuffled.
Punchline: Adds row probabilities to the Wondrous Tails display.

Author: Lady Defile
Name: Wordsmith
Description: Wordsmith is a text editor with roleplayers in mind. It automatically breaks your text up for easy copy/paste, has advanced features, spellcheck, and even a thesaurus.
Punchline: A roleplay thesaurus and scratch pad.

Author: HappySprite
Name: Workshop Optimizer Plugin
Description: Use /wso after you visited your island.
Punchline: Optimize Island Sanctuary Workshop orders.

Author: Anna
Name: XIVChat Server
Description:
XIVChat is a suite of software allowing you to use FFXIV's chat from
different devices. This is the server component required to do so.

For information about clients to use with this server, see the website.
Punchline: Use chat away from the game.

Author: Attick
Name: XIV Combo
Description: This plugin condenses combos and mutually exclusive abilities onto a single button. /pcombo to open menu
Punchline: PvP, but in PvE!

Author: Kaz Wolfe
Name: XIVDeck
Description:
This plugin allows players to use an Elgato Stream Deck as a virtual utility hot bar. Actions are called directly, meaning there is no need to set up awkward keybinds, custom macros, or any other settings.

Note that the XIVDeck Stream Deck plugin must also be installed for this plugin to be useful. You can download the Stream Deck plugin from the linked GitHub repository, under the "Releases" section.

Please report all problems to KazWolfe#2896 in the Dalamud Support server or by opening an Issue on GitHub.
Punchline: Turn your Elgato Stream Deck into a hotbar!

Author: CallumCarmicheal
Name: XIVDupeFinder
Description: Highlight stackable items in the inventory that are not stacked.
Punchline: Highlight duplicated items in inventories /xivdupes.

Author: Infi, Cadaeix
Name: XIVLogger
Description: Save chat logs as text files from when this is loaded. /xivlogger for settings, /savelog to save logs, /copylogs to copy logs.
Punchline: Save chat logs to your computer as text files or copy them!

Author: AlexCSDev
Name: XIVWindowResizer
Description:
Set your game window to arbitrary size not limited by your display resolution. Mostly useful for taking high-resolution screenshots without going fullscreen and using DSR/FSR.
Requires borderless or windowed mode.
Punchline: Game window resizing plugin. Ever wanted to take 8K screenshots on 144p screen? Now you can.

Author: daemitus, hiroa
Name: ZodiacBuddy
Description: This plugin attempts to help you complete your Zodiac weapon in various ways.
Punchline: Complete your Zodiac relic with style.
